def: A note of half the length of the quaver; a semiquaver. [R.]
A short, distorted hand; also, the deformity of having such ahand.
Produced by applying the tongue to the teeth or to the gums; orrepresenting a sound so formed.-- n.
The act of flowing forth; emanation; efflux. [Obs.] Dr. H.More.
One who assays. Specifically: One who examines metallic ores orcompounds, for the purpose of determining the amount of anyparticular metal in the same, especially of gold or silver.
An upholder of kingly authority; a royalist. [Obs.] Fuller.
